config BR2_PACKAGE_PANICOS_BOOTDIAG
	bool "panicos-bootdiag"
	depends on BR2_INIT_SYSTEMD
	help
	  Late-boot diagnostic dump. Runs once after multi-user.target
	  reaches active, then writes dmesg, journalctl, ip state, systemd
	  unit status, and DRM/wireless sysfs info to plain text files
	  under /boot/diag/ on the boot vfat. Pop the SD into a PC and
	  read the files to debug a board with no UART and no SSH.

	  Enable for bring-up; disable for production images. Off by default.

	  Marker file /boot/diag/done.txt is written last so you can tell
	  when it's safe to pull the SD.
